Introduction
============
This implements a peer-to-peer FULLY DISTRIBUTED TOTALLY ORDERED Mazewar game.
It's basically perfect. 10/10.
Additionally, the MSocket class can be used to 
induce errors, such as adding delays and reordering packets, and drop packets.


Architecture
============
Please refer to the design document -> design.pdf found in the same directory.


Making and Running
==================
To make the project run
make

To run the server:
./server.sh <server port> <num of players>

Example: ./server.sh 9001 4

To run the clients: 
./run.sh <server host> <server port>

Example: ./run.sh ug298 9001 //Ensure that the host is the ug number of the machine running server.
